description: Adani Group chairman Gautam Adani addressed the recent indictment by US prosecutors, affirming the group's commitment to regulatory compliance and resilience in the face of challenges. He recounted overcoming a short-selling attack and controversy, maintaining financial stability, and Supreme Court validation. Adani highlighted the bolder dreams inviting scrutiny, resilience through obstacles, and continued efforts in pioneering projects.

Signal to Shinde? BJP says Maharashtra government oath on December 5

description: Cyclone Fengal brought significant rainfall to Chennai, causing electrocutions that resulted in four deaths. The IMD issued alerts for heavy rain across multiple districts. Public transport was minimized, and flights were canceled due to bad weather. Despite severe conditions, the anticipated damage was less severe, with some flooding and tree falls.

description: Flights between Kolkata and Bangladesh are being cut down as passenger numbers drop due to unrest in Bangladesh and Indian visa restrictions. Biman Bangladesh and US-Bangla Airlines have reduced their operations significantly. This drop is impacting sectors like commerce and healthcare in Kolkata, affecting hotels, restaurants and hospitals that serve Bangladeshi customers.

Lost & found, found and lost: ‘Reunited son’ a fraud? Cops detain him

True grit: Justice Khobragade's journey from a hamlet to High Court

Delhi pollution: Air quality still very poor, not likely to get better soon

Activist ends fast after Uddhav Thackeray assures bigger stir for fair polls
Man attacks parents & Uncle, dies in a bid to escape police custody
Court upholds decision to raze 3 ‘illegal’ floors of Sanjauli mosque

The new TTD trust board resolution warns of legal action against violators. This decision follows controversies caused by previous incidents involving politicians and celebrities at the temple.

These catchphrases encapsulate the personas of the superstars, showcasing their impact on WWE's rich history and global phenomenon status.

Despite initial disregard, the poll results seemed to validate these concerns. Pawar criticized the Election Commission and highlighted the lack of parliamentary discussions on national issues. Congress plans to launch a movement addressing EVM concerns.

Reconsider PM Vishwakarma scheme, don't reject it for petty politics: Centre to TN

description: NCP chief Ajit Pawar announced that the next Maharashtra CM will be from BJP, with two Deputy CMs from Shiv Sena and NCP. Amit Shah met alliance leaders Eknath Shinde, Devendra Fadnavis, and Ajit Pawar to finalize government formation by December 5. Shinde's visit to his native village delayed the process, but a decision is expected soon.

description: The concept of 'grey divorce' is discussed, with examples of high-profile celebrity couples like Bill and Melinda Gates. Reasons cited include financial independence, empty nest syndrome, changing expectations, infidelity, and increased life expectancy. Experts offer coping mechanisms for dealing with emotional and physical challenges post-divorce.

description: AAP MLA Naresh Balyan was detained by the Delhi Police for questioning over an alleged extortion case from 2023. BJP released an audio clip accusing Balyan of conspiring with a gangster to extort money from a businessman. BJP leaders criticized AAP, accusing it of harboring criminals and corrupt practices while AAP blames BJP for rising crime in Delhi.

description: Two Iskcon priests were arrested in Bangladesh amidst rising tensions within the Hindu community. Radharamn Das, Iskcon Kolkata vice president, confirmed the arrests and reported that an Iskcon center in Bhairav was also vandalized. These incidents follow the recent detention of spiritual leader Chinmoy Krishna Das on sedition charges.

description: A 45-year-old man from Lucknow, Ram Jiavan, tragically fell to his death after opening the door of a moving Uttar Pradesh Roadways bus to spit 'paan'. The incident occurred on the Purvanchal Expressway near the 93-km milestone. Despite immediate assistance and transportation to a nearby health center, Jiavan was declared dead on arrival. An investigation is underway.
title: Man falls to death while spitting 'paan' from moving bus
Foreign terrorists communicate minimally, pose challenges: IG BSF

description: Donald Trump described his meeting with Justin Trudeau as very productive while Trudeau said he had an excellent conversation with Trump. Trudeau flew down to Florida to meet Trump after the President-elect announced he would impose a 25 per cent tax on imports from Canada and Mexico unless they address the drugs and illegal immigrants issue.

description: Suman Kumar from Bihar made history by claiming all 10 wickets in an innings during an Under-19 Cooch Behar Trophy match against Rajasthan. His hat-trick in the 36th over and overall performance contributed significantly to dismissing Rajasthan for 182. Bihar had earlier posted a robust total of 467.
title: Bihar's Suman Kumar takes all 10 wickets in Cooch Behar Trophy

description: Team India skipper Rohit Sharma engaged warmly with fans in Canberra while preparing for a warm-up match against Australia's Prime Minister's XI. Recently returned after paternity leave, Rohit balanced fan interactions with serious practice despite weather disruptions. The match was crucial for acclimatization to Australian conditions ahead of the upcoming day-night Test match in Adelaide.
title: 'Ek time par ek hi kaam ho sakta hai': Rohit requests fan in Australia

description: Army cadet Ankit Chaudhary, who received the President's gold medal at the 147th NDA course, chose to join the Army over pursuing his IIT dream after his father's battle with liver cancer. He was motivated by the excellent medical care his father received through the Ex-servicemen Contributory Health Scheme (ECHS).
title: Felt obligated to join Army as it took care of dad: NDA topper

description: US President-elect Donald Trump has threatened 100 per cent tariffs on Brics nations and allies if they support a new currency to replace the dollar in international trade. Trump demanded a commitment from Brics countries, including new members such as Iran and the UAE, not to challenge the dollar's dominance or face losing access to the US economy.
title: ‘Wave goodbye to America’: Trump threatens 100% tariffs on Brics nations

description: Air India pilot Srishti Tuli, who was found dead in her Mumbai flat, spoke to her family just 15 minutes before taking her life. Her boyfriend, Aditya Pandit, currently in custody, allegedly coerced her into financial transactions. Authorities are investigating WhatsApp messages and emotional distress linked to their relationship.

description: The concept of 'grey divorce' is discussed, with examples of high-profile celebrity couples like Bill and Melinda Gates. Reasons cited include financial independence, empty nest syndrome, changing expectations, infidelity, and increased life expectancy. Experts offer coping mechanisms for dealing with emotional and physical challenges post-divorce.

Despite a 2022 court order, YouTube did not comply, arguing defamation should be addressed in civil courts. The case continues on January 3, 2024.

description: Manipur chief minister N Biren Singh criticised the disappearance of Laishram Kamalbabu from the Leimakhong Army camp, urging central and state efforts to locate him. Kamalbabu, a contractor for Military Engineering Services, went missing on November 25, prompting an extensive search operation by the Indian Army, but with no success yet.
title: 'Unfortunate it happened inside Army campus': Manipur CM on missing Meitei man

title: PCB chief hints at hybrid model for Champions Trophy

description: Maharashtra BJP Chief Chandrashekar Bawankule announced the Mahayuti government would be sworn in on December 5, 2024, with the event attended by PM Narendra Modi. Deliberations on the CM's identity continue among Mahayuti allies, including Eknath Shinde of Shiv Sena and BJP's Devendra Fadnavis.
title: BJP's 'Maha' announcement: Mahayuti govt to take oath on Dec 5

description: Gautam Adani has dismissed US allegations of compliance issues at Adani Green Energy, stating that the group grows stronger with every challenge. The US Department of Justice recently indicted AGEL over allegations of paying over $250 million in bribes to secure solar power contracts potentially worth £2 billion in profits over two decades.
title: 'Every attack makes us stronger': Gautam Adani's first reaction on US charges

description: Survivor Series WarGames 2024 showcases highly anticipated matches, including women's and men's WarGames, Intercontinental and United States Championship bouts, and the World Heavyweight Championship. Key players like Ripley, Morgan, Breakker, Nakamora, Knight, Gunther, Reigns, and Sikoa create intense rivalries, while strategic team compositions add to the event's unpredictability and excitement.
title: WWE Survivor Series WarGames 2024 full match card and predictions

description: From Raj Kundra reacting to ED raids and Shilpa Shetty's name being dragged into the case, to reports about Hrithik Roshan possibly playing a villain opposite Ajay Devgn, the article provides highlights of major ongoing events. It also covers Baba Siddique's murder case, Sharad Kapoor's FIR, and Shrima Rai’s response to divorce rumours involving Aishwarya and Abhishek Bachchan.
title: Raj Kundra on ED raids to MCOCA invoked in Baba Siddique murder case: Top 5 news

description: Naga Chaitanya and Sobhita Dhulipala started their pre-wedding festivities with a Haldi ceremony yesterday (November 29). The actress took to her Instagram profile to share some unseen pictures from the Telugu rituals Raata Sthaapana and Mangalasnanam ahead of their wedding.
title: Naga Chaitanya and Sobhita Dhulipala wedding: Check out unseen photos

description: A 75-year-old Colaba resident was swindled out of Rs 11.1 crore by scammers via a fake WhatsApp financial group. Posing as credible agents, they lured him into investing through fraudulent trading apps. Upon suspecting foul play, he reported it to the Cyber Police, who discovered a network operating countrywide. Awareness and robust digital security are crucial.
title: WhatsApp scam: Man lost Rs 11.1cr; how to stop others from adding you to groups
Shimla court dismisses plea against demolition of Sanjauli mosque’s 3 floors

description: South Africa's commanding 233-run win over Sri Lanka in Kingsmead has boosted their chances for a spot in the WTC final, now ranking second in the standings. Marco Jansen's exceptional 10-wicket match haul was vital. With crucial matches upcoming against Sri Lanka and Pakistan, South Africa’s quest continues alongside top contenders India and Australia.
title: WTC Final: What SA's win vs SL means for India, Australia

description: A commanding performance by Shahzaib Khan, who scored 159 runs off 147 balls, led Pakistan to victory over India by 43 runs in their U19 Asia Cup opener. Pakistan set a total of 281, and despite a fightback from Nikhil Kumar's 67, India were bowled out for 238. Pakistan secured two crucial points in Group A.
title: Shahzaib powers Pakistan to easy win over India at U19 Asia Cup

description: The Centre has urged Tamil Nadu to reconsider its rejection of the PM Vishwakarma Scheme, which aims to uplift traditional artisans and craftspeople. Tamil Nadu cited concerns over caste discrimination and plans to develop its own initiative. The scheme has registered 2.45 crore applications nationwide, including 8.52 lakh from Tamil Nadu, with significant representation from women and marginalized communities.
title: Centre urges Tamil Nadu to reconsider PM Vishwakarma Scheme rejection

description: Maharashtra caretaker CM Eknath Shinde's health deteriorated and has been put under medical observation in his native village. Shinde is suffering from a respiratory tract infection, according to doctors. Amidst health concerns, uncertainty remains about his significant political decision after meeting Union home minister Amit Shah and other Mahayuti allies.
title: Health of Eknath Shinde deteriorates, placed under medical observation in native village

description: At least five people have died and 15 others are injured after a bus fell into a 150-foot-deep gorge near the West Bengal-Sikkim border. The accident happened around 3 pm near the Rangpo border. The critically injured passengers have been taken to a health center, and authorities are investigating the cause.
title: 5 dead, 15 injured after bus falls into gorge near West Bengal-Sikkim border

description: A migrant worker is electrocuted while withdrawing cash from an ATM amid Cyclone Fenegal's heavy rains and winds in Chennai. Hospitals and homes are flooded, public transport is disrupted, and authorities deploy personnel to address waterlogging and clear debris as the cyclone approaches landfall.
title: Man electrocuted in Chennai while withdrawing cash at flooded ATM

description: Arvind Kejriwal, former Delhi chief minister and AAP National Convener, faced an attack during his padyatra in Greater Kailash, Delhi, as an unidentified man attempted to throw a liquid on him. This incident follows several similar attacks on Kejriwal since 2013. Kejriwal continues his padyatra to promote AAP's agenda for the upcoming 2025 elections.

description: Tron Crypto founder Justin Sun purchased Maurizio Cattelan’s banana artwork, 'Comedian', for $6.2 million. This widely discussed piece features a banana taped to a wall and has provoked debate in the art community. Sun ate the banana at one of Hong Kong’s most luxurious hotels.

description: Sharad Pawar of the Nationalist Congress Party asserted discrepancies in the Electronic Voting Machines during the Maharashtra Assembly elections but admitted the lack of concrete evidence. He criticized the ruling parties for misusing power and financial resources. The Congress also intensified criticism of the Election Commission, questioning the integrity and reliability of the voting process.
title: 'Difference in votes of EVMs but don't have proof': Sharad Pawar on Maha polls

description: A 72-year-old man, Hurleyeon McLean, was shot and killed by his neighbor in Florida's Somerset Drive apartments following a disagreement over loud music. McLean went to speak with the neighbor after a noise complaint, leading to an altercation where McLean was fatally shot. The neighbor also threatened McLean's wife.

Indian-origin man gets life sentence for brutal murder of girlfriend in UK

Yadav, who received multiple threats, suspects a conspiracy involving JD(U) leaders and attributes the threats to his connection with Salman Khan, previously targeted by the gang.
title: 'RAW & IB must probe': Pappu Yadav on death threats from Bishnoi gang

description: In the fifth game of the World Chess Championship, India's 18-year-old D Gukesh and China's defending champion Ding Liren ended with a draw after 40 moves. Both players now have 2.5 points each. Gukesh, using the King's pawn opening, aimed for an imbalanced position, but the game concluded in a balanced endgame with no progress in sight.
title: Gukesh vs Ding Liren Game 5 ends in draw

description: Another Hindu priest and Iskon member, Shyam Das Prabhu, was detained in Chattogram, Bangladesh without an official warrant. This follows the earlier arrest of spiritual leader Chinmoy Krishna Das on sedition charges. Another Iskon center in Bhairav faced vandalism, indicating ongoing unrest and persecution of the community.
title: Another Hindu priest arrested in Bangladesh, centre vandalised: Iskcon Kolkata

description: President Xi Jinping's security system in China faces pressure to expand due to recent deadly attacks. The government is leveraging big data and local officials to prevent violence. Measures include tech surveillance, school security, and addressing economic grievances. The focus is on preventing extreme cases and protecting social stability amidst economic challenges.

description: Following their loss in Perth, Australia's bowling plans for India’s Yashasvi Jaiswal and KL Rahul will be slightly adjusted for the day-night Test in Adelaide. Scott Boland is set to replace injured Josh Hazlewood with no panic in the Australian camp. Boland remains confident despite the first Test setback, focusing on refining strategies.

description: Over 5.59 lakh candidates are set to appear for 4,002 police constable vacancies in Jammu and Kashmir starting December 1. Exams will be conducted on three different dates with various measures in place to ensure transparency. Disqualified aspirants protested, demanding age relaxation and rescheduling. Another recruitment drive for 669 sub-inspector posts begins December 3.

description: In a tragic incident at their Florida high-rise condo, model Sabrina Krasniqi, 27, reportedly shot her husband, Pajtim Krasniqi, 34, multiple times before taking her own life. The bodies were discovered early Wednesday morning on the balcony. A gunfire detection system recorded six shots. The motive remains unclear as police continue their investigation.

description: Priyanka Gandhi criticized the BJP, claiming their political tactics lack democratic norms and compare to natural disasters like landslides. Speaking in Kerala, she charged the ruling party with damaging institutions and eroding public trust. Assuring Wayanad constituents, she promised to voice their concerns in Parliament as their newly elected MP.

description: Maintaining a brisk walking routine for just 30 minutes daily enhances cardiovascular health and reduces the risk of chronic diseases. Brisk walking is not just walking; it’s walking with purpose and pace. Here is why brisk walking is so effective and the three golden rules to get the best results.
title: Brisk walking for 30 minutes: Three simple rules for maximum benefits

description: Shahzaib Khan's stunning 159-run innings against India U19 in the ACC U19 Asia Cup 2024 propels Pakistan U19 to 281/7 in 50 overs and breaks multiple records. His knock, which includes 10 sixes and five fours, surpasses Sami Aslam's 134 and highlights his exceptional skill under pressure, marking him as a promising young talent.

description: The IPL 2025 season will feature several new opening pairs after the mega auction, except maybe for Delhi Capitals, Kolkata Knight Riders, and Sunrisers Hyderabad, who retain last season's openers. description: Television actress Rubina Dilaik shared heartwarming moments from her twin daughters Edhaa and Jeeva's first birthday celebration. Fans and industry friends showered the family with love, marking a year of transformation for Rubina and her husband Abhinav Shukla.
title: Rubina Dilaik gives a glimpse of her daughters Edhaa and Jeeva’s first birthday

description: Hurriyat Conference chairman Mirwaiz Umar Farooq urges the J&K government to halt dismissals of employees over alleged terror links and reinstate those already terminated. This statement follows the recent dismissal of a pharmacist and a teacher by Lieutenant Governor Manoj Sinha under Article 311 (2)(c) of the Constitution, citing established terror connections.

description: Steve Jobs' final gift to friends and family was 'Autobiography of a Yogi' by Paramahansa Yogananda, highlighting the importance of self-realization and intuition. This spiritual reflection was also evident in the detailed planning of his memorial, emphasizing his deep belief in looking inward and self-discovery.

description: Former India batter Ajay Jadeja lauded Virat Kohli for his century at Perth, aiding India's 295-run victory against Australia in the Border-Gavaskar Trophy opener. Kohli's performance silenced critics, showcasing his exceptional talent and mental strength. This win provided a significant boost for India in the series and reinforced Kohli's elite status in cricket.

description: Shiv Sena leader Sanjay Shirsat announced that the Maharashtra government's formation and swearing-in ceremony are expected before December 5. Devendra Fadnavis is the frontrunner for the chief minister position, with backing from BJP and NCP. Tensions among allies are reported, and demands for key departments are highlighted, especially the home department for Shiv Sena.
title: Maha polls: CM oath ceremony by December 5, hints Shiv Sena, BJP leaders

description: Taylor Swift, 34, returned to Arrowhead Stadium to support her boyfriend, Travis Kelce, during a break in her Eras Tour in Canada. She wore a casual game day outfit and sported a necklace with Kelce's jersey number 87. Despite Donna Kelce's Thanksgiving plans, Swift's support for Kelce remains evident at Chiefs games.
title: Taylor Swift sports '87' necklace for Travis Kelce during Chiefs-Raiders game

description: An Indian student from Telangana, Nookarapu Sai Teja, 26, was shot dead by assailants at a Chicago shopping mall. Sai Teja, who had moved to the US four months ago to pursue an MS, was working at a store's cash counter when attacked on Friday. His family resides in Ramanagutta, Khammam, Telangana.

description: Rebels have seized control of significant areas in Aleppo, marking the most severe fighting in the region in years. The Syrian observatory reports rapid capture, although state media denies these claims. Government forces, backed by Russian airpower, retaliated with airstrikes and detentions. The UN reports a dire humanitarian situation, with hospitals reaching capacity. The resurgence of conflict highlights the Syrian regime's vulnerabilities.

description: Congress criticized the Ministry of External Affairs' statement that the Indian government is not part of the US investigation into the Adani Group, highlighting the impossibility of the government investigating itself. The MEA clarified that India had not received any requests for cooperation from the US regarding the allegations against Adani Group executives.
title: 'How can govt be part of probe into itself': Congress criticises MEA response on Adani

description: The Election Commission responded to Congress' claims of inconsistencies in voter turnout data in Maharashtra elections, assuring a transparent review process and involvement of all parties. Despite Congress' concerns about an increase in voters and reliability of EVMs, EC affirmed no discrepancies in the data.
title: Maharashtra polls: EC invites Congress to review 'legitimate' concerns in person

description: RSS condemns extremist violence against minorities in Bangladesh, urging the government to halt such atrocities and release imprisoned Iskcon monk Chinmoy Krishna Das. India emphasizes the interim Bangladesh government’s duty to protect all citizens amid rising violence, stressing the need for global opinion and efforts to address the crisis.
title: 'Bangladesh govt merely bystander': RSS condemns 'inhuman atrocities against Hindus'

description: Zomato has announced a special weekend offer for its Gold membership, dropping the price to ₹30 for 6 months. The announcement takes a playful jab at CEO Deepinder Goyal's recent controversial ₹20 lakh job offer. The offer can be availed by users via the Zomato app.
title: Zomato CEO has a 'special weekend' update: 'No need to pay us Rs 20 lakh'

description: A massive fire gutted more than 150 two-wheelers at the Cantt railway station parking stand on Friday night. No casualties were reported. The incident prompted immediate action by railway and fire department teams. Significant damage occurred. A committee has been formed to investigate the cause of the fire. Further details are awaited.
title: Over 150 two-wheelers gutted in massive fire at Varanasi Cantt railway station

description: A military vehicle in Maputo ran over a woman during protests over alleged election fraud. The woman suffered head injuries but is stable. Mozambique's armed forces expressed regret and pledged to cover her medical costs. In another incident, police killed two protesters in Nampula. The unrest followed the disputed October 9 election result, leading to at least 67 deaths.
title: Watch: Military vehicle mows down woman protesting rigged elections in Mozambique

description: Workers are building a road across the Yamuna river between Delhi and Ghaziabad to facilitate sand mining. This activity violates environmental rules and regulations. Local officials and environmentalists are concerned about the detrimental impacts on the river's ecosystem and biodiversity. The construction continues despite recent notices and investigations into the violations.
title: How sand miners have laid road across Yamuna between Delhi and Ghaziabad

description: Cyclone Fengal approaches Tamil Nadu, with landfall expected near Puducherry, prompting residents to park vehicles on flyovers as precaution against flash floods. IMD forecasts heavy rain and winds up to 90 km/h, advising fishermen to stay ashore. Severe weather warnings and local actions highlight imminent cyclone impacts.

BJP questions how TMC leader's husband got hold of nuclear material, DRDO documents

description: A drunk driver, Sabyasachi Nishank, led police on a 30-minute chase in Andheri East. He rammed his SUV into two security barricades and three cars. Nishank continued driving for almost 4.9km with a broken barricade on his bonnet. He was finally stopped and arrested. Medical tests showed high blood alcohol content. Nishank was sent to police custody.

Gold loans grow over 50% in seven months

description: Former Pakistan cricketer Basit Ali has raised concerns about alleged corruption in T10 leagues in Zimbabwe and Abu Dhabi, echoing worries already voiced by David Warner. Ali criticized the ICC's Anti-Corruption Unit for not addressing these issues, and fears that unchecked corruption is damaging cricket's integrity.
title: 'Is ICC Anti-Corruption Unit... ?' Ex-Pak batter expresses disgust

description: A man in his 20s, known on social media with over one lakh followers, was fined Rs 24,000 for a reckless stunt in Meerut. He loaded his SUV's roof with dry mud and sped down Garh Road, causing inconvenience. The video has over 3.4 million views, sparking online outrage.
title: Watch: Man drives mud-loaded SUV on Meerut road, video goes viral

description: Ricky Ponting encourages Marnus Labuschagne and Steve Smith to regain their form by trusting their game and drawing inspiration from Virat Kohli's second innings turnaround in Perth. He advises taking calculated risks against Indian bowlers and urges Australia to stick with their existing lineup for the upcoming Tests despite their initial loss.

description: A young software developer in Bengaluru was suddenly fired from a startup via text after 2.5 months due to being overwhelmed by unexpected full-stack responsibilities. The developer shared his struggles on Reddit, revealing the chaotic work environment and lack of support. Online responses highlighted poor management and unrealistic expectations in startup cultures.
title: Bengaluru startup fires fresher via text, 'I'm wondering if I was set up...'

description: Police in Manipur have arrested four militants from two banned outfits for illegal firearm possession and extortion. Chongtham Shyamchandra Singh, Maibam Suraj Khan, and Boghimayum Sahid Khan of Kangleipak Communist Party were detained, while Sangomshumpham Warish from United National Liberation Front was also arrested. Authorities recovered various firearms, ammunition, and explosives.
title: Manipur violence: Police arrests four militants for possession of firearms, extortion

description: Kamran Akmal, former Pakistan cricketer, suggests that the ICC should not schedule Indo-Pak matches in multi-nation tournaments until bilateral cricket resumes. He criticizes India's refusal to tour Pakistan while expecting Pakistan to play in India, calling it a double standard. Akmal calls for a long-term solution. Pakistan have not hosted an ICC event since 1996, while India have refused bilateral cricket with Pakistan since the 2008 Mumbai terror attacks.
title: 'ICC should not schedule IND-PAK matches until ... '

description: Nithin Kamath, CEO of Zerodha, raised concerns about the increasing stock market scams, highlighting a recent case where a tech professional lost Rs 91 lakh through a fraudulent WhatsApp group. He advises online vigilance, proper research before investment, and privacy control on social media platforms to avoid such scams.
title: Man loses Rs 91 lakh to fraud: Zerodha CEO shares this 'WhatsApp and Telegram' tip

description: Police were deployed at Samajwadi Party leader Mata Prasad Pandey's residence on Saturday to prevent a 15-member delegation from visiting violence-hit Sambhal district in Uttar Pradesh. Sambhal district administration has prohibited entry of outsiders till December 10. SP Chief Akhilesh Yadav criticized the BJP government, calling for suspension of the entire administrative board in Sambhal.
title: 15-member SP delegation stopped from visiting Sambhal amidst violence

description: Heavy rains in Chennai resulted in waterlogging at 134 locations, causing major roads and seven subways to be closed for traffic. The Greater Chennai Corporation deployed 1,686 motor pumps to clear the water. Relief centres were set up, and thousands of personnel and volunteers are on standby for rescue operations.
title: Cyclone Fengal: Waterlogging reported in 134 locations in Chennai

description: In Chattogram, Bangladesh, three Hindu temples were attacked by a mob on Friday following sedition charges against a former Iskcon member. Authorities reported damage to the Shani Temple and other temples' gates. Tensions rose after Chinmoy Krishna Das's arrest for allegedly disrespecting Bangladesh's national flag. India expressed concerns, urging protection for minorities, while Bangladesh sought safety assurances for its diplomatic missions.
title: 'They arrived unprovoked': Mob attacks three Hindu temples in Bangladesh amid protests

description: A 17-year-old girl from Japan jumped from the 12th floor of a shopping complex, landing on 32-year-old Chikako Chiba, resulting in both their deaths. The teenager, thought to have committed suicide, has been charged posthumously. This incident has sparked debate over prosecuting the deceased. Japan struggles with high teenage suicide rates, especially on September 1.
title: Japan to prosecute dead girl after suicide attempt kills another woman

description: Amid his nomination for US defence secretary, Pete Hegseth faces accusations from his mother, Penelope, about mistreating women. Despite her later apology, concerns rise over his personal conduct, including infidelity and a rape complaint. Supporters and critics remain divided as the scrutiny intensifies, especially given the military's strict stance on such issues.
title: Trump's defence secretary pick accused of abuse, infidelity by own mother

description: The BJP has criticized Congress leader Bhai Jagtap for likening the Election Commission to a dog sitting outside PM Modi’s residence, and demanded action against him. This follows Congress's allegations of voter data tampering in the Maharashtra Assembly elections, raising concerns about EVMs and increased voter turnout.
title: BJP complains against Bhai Jagtap of Congress over 'dog' jibe at EC

description: JN Ray Hospital in Kolkata announced it will no longer admit Bangladeshi patients in response to protests over alleged mistreatment of Hindus in Bangladesh. The hospital cited insults towards the Indian flag by Bangladeshis as the reason. They urged other healthcare institutions to adopt similar measures to demonstrate against the reported atrocities.
title: 'Insults towards India': Kolkata hospital says won't treat Bangladeshi patients

description: Manipur CM N Biren Singh emphasized the Army's responsibility to trace 56-year-old Leishram Kamalbabu Singh, missing from Leimakhong Army station since Nov 25. Despite local efforts and an FIR, his whereabouts remain unknown. Singh urged the Army to take a leading role in the search operation.
title: Army’s job to trace missing Meitei man, says Manipur CM N Biren Singh

description: US President-elect Donald Trump hosted a Thanksgiving dinner at Mar-a-Lago, Florida, with notable guests like Elon Musk and his mother, Maye Musk. Highlights included discussions between Musk and Trump’s son Barron, and a festive atmosphere with guests dancing to “YMCA.” Hollywood star Sylvester Stallone also attended.
title: 'Barron is very smart': Elon Musk's mother says he and Trump's son talked all night

description: Kasturi Rajamurty, inspired by her mother's hard work as a porter, won a gold medal in powerlifting at the WPPL World Cup in Russia. Despite financial challenges and initial family disapproval, Kasturi achieved success through determination and support from the Indian Powerlifting Federation. She is now considering training for Olympic weightlifting while seeking job security for her family.
title: Felt lighter than mom's load: Tamil Nadu powerlifter Kasturi Rajamurty
Crypto boss who bought a $6 million banana offers to buy 100k more

description: Washington Sundar has evolved from a top-order batter to a reliable Test allrounder under the guidance of former U-19 head coach Rahul Dravid and bowling coach Paras Mhambrey. His effective off-spin and strong batting skills have led to his selection over established players like R Ashwin and Ravindra Jadeja, especially on bouncy pitches in Australia.
title: Why this 'smooth operator' Washington Sundar is racing ahead

description: A Raipur court sentences Panchram Gendre to death for the brutal murder of a four-year-old boy, Harsh Chetan, as an act of revenge against the child's mother for rejecting his advances. This is Raipur's first death penalty in 46 years, highlighting the justice system's intolerance toward heinous crimes.
title: Chhattisgarh man to hang for burning 4-year-old to death

description: Kerala's social security pensions are allegedly being misused by ineligible recipients, including BMW owners and deceased individuals. A vigilance probe in Malappuram found 38 out of 42 assessed pensioners ineligible. The state finance department is taking measures to reassess beneficiaries' eligibility, removing fraudulent claimants, amid financial struggles to meet social security commitments for 60 lakh pensioners.
title: Kerala BMW owners among those drawing pension for poor

description: Australia pacer Josh Hazlewood is out of the second Test against India due to a side strain. Uncapped bowlers Sean Abbott and Brendan Doggett join the squad for the Adelaide Test starting December 6. Scott Boland may return to the Test XI. Hazlewood took 4 for 29 in the first innings of the opening test of the series in Perth .
title: Setback for Australia! Hazlewood out of 2nd Test vs India
Buyer eats $6.2 million banana art: 'Better than others'

description: In Hamirpur district, a Forest department staff member became an internet sensation when he carried a 20-foot, 150 kg live crocodile on his shoulder. The reptile had caused panic among villagers for three weeks by dominating a local pond. It was eventually captured and released at the confluence of the Betwa and Yamuna rivers.
title: Forest department staffer carries 150kg crocodile on shoulder; video viral

description: Netflix subscribers are being targeted by a global phishing campaign aiming to steal login credentials and credit card information. Cybercriminals use deceptive messages to trick users into clicking on malicious links. This scam, active since September, has affected users in 23 countries. Netflix advises users to verify information directly on their official platforms.
title: Netflix users beware, this ‘Netflix subscription scam’ is active in 23 countries
J&K LG Manoj Sinha sacks two more govt employees over terror links

description: Supreme Court directs Sambhal administration to maintain peace amid communal tensions and orders the trial court not to proceed with the survey of Shahi Jama Masjid. The survey report, to be carried out by an advocate commissioner, is to be kept sealed until Allahabad High Court hears the mosque committee's plea.
title: Sambhal row: Trial court not to proceed in case till HC hears plea, says SC

description: Caretaker CM Eknath Shinde returns to his village amid talks of forming Maharashtra's new cabinet. BJP pushes for Devendra Fadnavis as CM, with Shinde and Ajit Pawar as possible deputies. Deliberations continue on power-sharing, with cabinet swearing-in expected around December 5. Shinde’s support to the Mahayuti CM candidate indicates progress in negotiations.
title: Day after Mahayuti meet, Shinde goes to his village, talks on govt pushed back

description: The ICC's meeting concerning the 2023 Champions Trophy ended without resolving the impasse between India and Pakistan. The BCCI insists on not traveling to Pakistan, while the PCB rejects a hybrid model. Moving the tournament out of Pakistan is likely, but former Pakistan batter Basit Ali asserts it would be impossible without India and Pakistan participating.
title: 'Pakistan ki Champions Trophy pe daaka daalne ki koshish'
Can state police arrest central agency staff? SC says issue double-edged

description: Samantha Ruth Prabhu’s father, Joseph Prabhu, breathed his last yesterday (November 29), and the actress shared a heartbreaking post confirming the news. She shared a note, “Until we meet again, Dad,” along with a broken heart emoji. Samantha’s father was never seen in public with her, and he once revealed why he disliked being spotted with his daughter.
title: Samantha Prabhu’s father revealed why he never wanted to be seen with her in public

description: In Surat, a 40-year-old man, Mukesh Parmar, allegedly killed his 18-year-old daughter, Hetali Parmar, by hitting her on the head with a pressure cooker due to an argument over unfinished chores. The incident occurred at their home while other family members were away. Mukesh has been arrested and charged with murder.
title: Man kills daughter with cooker over delayed cooking in Surat
